# Project Context — Discord Clone

## What this is
A realtime text chat platform built around servers and channels.
Target: CV project demonstrating hybrid DB architecture, realtime systems, and clean NestJS structure.
Scale target: CV-level, not production. Optimise for code clarity and correct architecture over performance.

## Tech stack
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | NestJS (TypeScript) |
| Relational DB | PostgreSQL via Drizzle ORM |
| Document DB | MongoDB via Mongoose |
| Realtime | Socket.IO (NestJS Gateway) |
| Auth | JWT (access token only, no refresh for MVP) |

## Core domain concepts
- **Server (Guild)** — a community space, has an owner
- **Channel** — a text channel inside a server
- **Membership** — a user belonging to a server
- **Message** — a single chat message, stored in MongoDB

## The architectural argument (CV talking point)
PostgreSQL handles relational data and permission checks — things that need consistency and joins.
MongoDB handles messages — high-volume, append-heavy, queried always by channelId.
The split is justified by access pattern, not fashion.
**This argument only holds if the boundary is maintained in code.**

## MVP scope — done means done
- [ ] Auth (register, login, JWT)
- [ ] Server CRUD (create, join via invite, list)
- [ ] Channel CRUD (create inside server, list)
- [ ] Send message (realtime via socket)
- [ ] Load message history (cursor pagination)
- [ ] Basic permission (membership check before send)

## Out of scope — do not implement
- Voice / video
- File/image uploads
- Role matrix (beyond owner vs member)
- Push notifications
- Read receipts
- Message editing / deletion (nice-to-have, not MVP)
